# Local Data Stack - Daily Pipeline Execution
# 
# Crontab entry for automated data pipeline scheduling
# 
# Installation:
#   1. Edit crontab: crontab -e
#   2. Copy the line below (uncomment it by removing the leading #)
#   3. Save and exit
# 
# Verification:
#   crontab -l  # List current crontab entries
# 
# Logs:
#   Logs are written to oss_framework/logs/cron.log
#   View with: tail -f /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack/oss_framework/logs/cron.log

# ============================================================================
# DAILY PIPELINE EXECUTION - 6 AM
# ============================================================================

# Run data pipeline every day at 6:00 AM
0 6 * * * cd /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack && ./scripts/schedule_pipeline.sh >> oss_framework/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# ============================================================================
# ALTERNATIVE SCHEDULES (uncomment one if needed)
# ============================================================================

# Every 6 hours (at 00:00, 06:00, 12:00, 18:00)
# 0 */6 * * * cd /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack && ./scripts/schedule_pipeline.sh >> oss_framework/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Weekdays only at 6 AM (Monday-Friday)
# 0 6 * * 1-5 cd /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack && ./scripts/schedule_pipeline.sh >> oss_framework/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Weekly on Sunday at 2 AM
# 0 2 * * 0 cd /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack && ./scripts/schedule_pipeline.sh >> oss_framework/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Hourly (at minute 0 of every hour)
# 0 * * * * cd /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack && ./scripts/schedule_pipeline.sh >> oss_framework/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# ============================================================================
# LOG CLEANUP (optional - run weekly)
# ============================================================================

# Archive old logs every Sunday at 3 AM
# 0 3 * * 0 find /Users/flucido/projects/local-data-stack/oss_framework/logs -name "*.log" -mtime +30 -exec gzip {} \;

# ============================================================================
# CRON SYNTAX REFERENCE
# ============================================================================
#
# ┌───────────── minute (0-59)
# │ ┌───────────── hour (0-23)
# │ │ ┌───────────── day of month (1-31)
# │ │ │ ┌───────────── month (1-12)
# │ │ │ │ ┌───────────── day of week (0-7, 0 and 7 = Sunday)
# │ │ │ │ │
# * * * * * command to execute
#
# Examples:
#   0 6 * * *       Every day at 6:00 AM
#   0 */6 * * *     Every 6 hours
#   0 6 * * 1-5     Weekdays at 6:00 AM
#   0 0 1 * *       First day of month at midnight
#   */15 * * * *    Every 15 minutes
